    <p>{`When enabled on a service, Intelligent Alert Grouping will automatically add incoming alerts to related open incidents on that service to help keep responders focused on the problem at hand. Once Intelligent Alert Grouping has been enabled on a service, the first new incoming alert will create a new incident. The underlying algorithm will then determine which, if any, subsequent alerts should be grouped into existing incidents.  Once an incident is closed, no new alerts will be added to it. `}</p>
    <p>{`The Intelligent Alert Grouping algorithm includes a real-time, machine-learning-based model that is designed to quickly and accurately process and cluster machine-generated data on each service. The algorithm will adapt over time to understand new types of alerts and react to human response behavior. `}</p>
