            "d": "M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"
          }}></path></svg></a>{`Can Intelligent Alert Grouping group alerts together from multiple services?`}</h3>
    <p>{`Not at the moment. Intelligent Alert Grouping only looks at alerts from a single service. If you want alerts from different services to be grouped, you may need to reconfigure your service so that all related alerts are sent to the same service. For best practices, please see our `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://community.pagerduty.com/t/service-configuration-guide/5110"
      }}>{`Service Configuration Guide`}</a>{`. `}</p>
